# Service Drift Guardrails

Use these non-negotiable policies to prevent backend, frontend, and service drift.

## Required guardrails

- Keep backend and frontend API contracts in sync within the same task. If backend schema, routes, payloads, or response shapes change, update generated clients/types and callers in that same change.
- Keep one canonical committed environment defaults/examples file: `.env.local.example`.
- For bugs and regressions, fix root cause first. Avoid workaround-only patches unless explicitly requested.
- Do not mark work done or ready until `make ci` passes from repository root.

## PR-ready checklist

- [ ] Backend and frontend contract changes are synchronized.
- [ ] Environment variable changes are reflected in `.env.local.example` only.
- [ ] Root cause and regression risk are addressed.
- [ ] `make ci` passes.
